This paper deals with privacy concerns in community reviewing, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to analyze the data, which could place it under the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of its findings for cross-referencing accounts between different review sites, which could place it under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also uses data mining techniques to analyze the reviews, which could place it under the sub-category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the feedback that review sites could give to contributors about the privacy of their reviews, which could place it under the sub-category of software development (cs.SD).
